fields.description:
I have a project with 3 submodules and often I update several submodules. I push with

{code}
git push --recurse-submodules=on-demand
{code}

Every other time bitbucket can&#x27;t accept payload:

{code}
[:~/prj[master]]$ git push --recurse-submodules=on-demand
Pushing submodule &#x27;extra&#x27;
Counting objects: 5, done.
Delta compression using up to 8 threads.
Compressing objects: 100% (3/3), done.
Writing objects: 100% (3/3), 343 bytes, done.
Total 3 (delta 2), reused 0 (delta 0)
To git@bitbucket.org:user/prj_extra.git
   236466a..edfcea3  master -> master
Pushing submodule &#x27;unittests&#x27;
fatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly
error: push died of signal 13
Unable to push submodule &#x27;unittests&#x27;
fatal: Failed to push all needed submodules!
[:~/prj[master]]$ fatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly
{code}

My SSH public key contains &#x27;é&#x27; (in my username). When I try to add it using the "add key" form, nothing happens after I click the "add" button.

My key:

{code}
ssh-rsa  René Fleschenberg <rene@fleschenberg.net>
{code}

As a workaround, I changed my name to "Rene" in the form.

In [this commit|https://bitbucket.org/mg/bitbucket-test/commits/a448e9f66fde], I wrote

{code}
URLs and quotes: &#x27;http://example.net/&#x27;
{code}

as the commit message. Bitbucket recognized the URL and turned it into a link (incorrectly, the link points to {{http://example.net/&#x27;}}, with the final single-quote). The link text was double-escaped so that it became

{code}
http://example.net/&amp;#39
{code}

in the source (without the backslash, that is bug BCLOUD-7478).

The results of the above command you posted is the following\\
MacBook-Pro:Mainrepo.git username$ git push -u origin --all --verbose Pushing to ssh://git@bitbucket.org/NAMEOFGIT.git Counting objects: 600, done. Delta compression using up to 8 threads. Compressing objects: 100% (567/567), done. Received disconnect from 207.223.240.181: 2: Packet corrupt fatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly error: pack-objects died of signal 13 error: failed to push some refs to &#x27;ssh://git@bitbucket.org/NAMEOFGIT.git&#x27;

I tried starting from a fresh repo and pushing changes and was unsuccessful there too. Following are the results\\
user-64-9-235-121:.git username$ git push -u origin master Counting objects: 865, done. Delta compression using up to 8 threads. Compressing objects: 100% (856/856), done. Received disconnect from 207.223.240.182: 2: Packet corrupt fatal: The remote end hung up unexpectedly error: pack-objects died of signal 13 error: failed to push some refs to &#x27;ssh://git@bitbucket.org/NameOfREpo.git&#x27;

This was on Mac OS X 10.8 using iTerm2 , if that makes any difference.

I have a [wiki page|https://bitbucket.org/tlroche/aqmeii-na_n2o/wiki/N2O_emission_inventories_over_AQMEII-NA_2008] which cites [a URI with an anchor beginning with the numeral &#x27;12&#x27;|http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/methodology.php#12sou]:

{code}
References:

* [[http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/index.php|EDGAR homepage]]
* [[http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/overview.php?v=42|EDGAR-4.2 overview]]
* [[http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/methodology.php#12sou|EDGAR-4.2 categories]]
* [[https://bitbucket.org/tlroche/edgar-4.2_minus_soil_and_biomass_to_aqmeii-na|my project for assimilating non-agricultural-soil EDGAR inventories]]
{code}

Unfortunately, your parser appears to be attempting to render this as a reference to a bitbucket issue:

{code}
#!HTML

References:</p>
<ul><li><a href="http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/index.php">EDGAR homepage</a>
</li><li><a href="http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/overview.php?v=42">EDGAR-4.2 overview</a>
</li><li><a href="/tlroche/aqmeii-na_n2o/wiki/http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/methodology.php%3C%3Cissue%2012%3E%3Esou">EDGAR-4.2 categories</a>
</li><li><a href="https://bitbucket.org/tlroche/edgar-4.2_minus_soil_and_biomass_to_aqmeii-na">my project for assimilating non-agricultural-soil EDGAR inventories</a>
</li></ul>

{code}

I.e., the markup link

{code}
[[http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/methodology.php#12sou|EDGAR-4.2 categories]]
{code}

should render as

{code}
#!HTML
<a href="http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/methodology.php#12sou">EDGAR-4.2 categories</a>
{code}

but is instead rendering as

{code}
#!HTML
<a href="/tlroche/aqmeii-na_n2o/wiki/http://edgar.jrc.ec.europa.eu/methodology.php%3C%3Cissue%2012%3E%3Esou">EDGAR-4.2 categories</a>
{code}

Please fix.

There used to be links at the bottom of the commits page that says:

{code}
#!
1  2  3  4  5 ... 11
{code}

These links let me quickly browse the commits without using a mercurial client. However, it seems to be missing recently, perhaps after a recent bit bucket update.

Please add it back.
